        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","collaborate - 合作，协作","The two companies decided to collaborate on the project. 两家公司决定在这个项目上合作。\n搭配: collaborate with 与...合作\n同义词: cooperate, work together","v. collaborates, collaborating, collaborated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","compassion - 同情，怜悯","She showed great compassion for the homeless. 她对无家可归者表现出极大的同情。\n搭配: have compassion for 对...有同情心\n同义词: sympathy, mercy","n. (uncountable)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","compel - 强迫，迫使","The evidence compelled the jury to find him guilty. 证据迫使陪审团认定他有罪。\n搭配: compel sb. to do sth. 迫使某人做某事\n同义词: force, oblige","v. compels, compelling, compelled","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","complement - 补充，补足，配套","The wine complements the meal perfectly. 这瓶酒完美地搭配了这顿饭。\n搭配: complement each other 互补\n同义词: supplement, complete","n./v. complements, complementing, complemented","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","comprehensive - 全面的，综合的","The report provides a comprehensive analysis of the market. 报告提供了对市场的全面分析。\n搭配: comprehensive study 综合研究\n同义词: thorough, complete","adj. comprehensively (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","compromise - 妥协，折中，危害","They reached a compromise after long negotiations. 经过长时间谈判他们达成了妥协。\n搭配: reach a compromise 达成妥协\n同义词: concession, settlement","n./v. compromises, compromising, compromised","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","concede - 承认，让步，给予","He conceded that he had made a mistake. 他承认自己犯了错误。\n搭配: concede defeat 承认失败\n同义词: admit, acknowledge","v. concedes, conceding, conceded","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","condemn - 谴责，判刑","The international community condemned the terrorist attack. 国际社会谴责了这次恐怖袭击。\n搭配: condemn sb. for sth. 因某事谴责某人\n同义词: criticize, denounce","v. condemns, condemning, condemned","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","confidential - 机密的，保密的","All medical records are strictly confidential. 所有医疗记录都严格保密。\n搭配: confidential information 机密信息\n同义词: secret, private","adj. confidentially (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","conform - 符合，遵守，顺从","All products must conform to safety standards. 所有产品必须符合安全标准。\n搭配: conform to 符合\n同义词: comply, adhere","v. conforms, conforming, conformed","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","confront - 面对，遭遇，对抗","We must confront the challenges ahead. 我们必须面对前方的挑战。\n搭配: confront with 面对\n同义词: face, encounter","v. confronts, confronting, confronted","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","conscious - 有意识的，自觉的","She was conscious of being watched. 她意识到被人注视。\n搭配: be conscious of 意识到\n同义词: aware, mindful","adj. consciously (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","consensus - 共识，一致意见","The committee reached a consensus on the proposal. 委员会就该提案达成了共识。\n搭配: reach a consensus 达成共识\n同义词: agreement, unanimity","n. (uncountable)","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","consent - 同意，准许，赞成","She gave her consent to the surgery. 她同意了手术。\n搭配: give consent 给予同意\n同义词: agree, approve","n./v. consents, consenting, consented","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","consequence - 结果，后果，重要性","You must accept the consequences of your actions. 你必须接受自己行为的后果。\n搭配: as a consequence 结果\n同义词: result, outcome","n. consequences","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","conservative - 保守的，传统的","He holds conservative views on social issues. 他在社会问题上持保守观点。\n搭配: conservative estimate 保守估计\n同义词: traditional, cautious","adj./n. conservatively (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","considerable - 相当大的，重要的","The project requires considerable investment. 这个项目需要相当大的投资。\n搭配: considerable amount 相当大的数量\n同义词: significant, substantial","adj. considerably (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","consistent - 一致的，始终如一的","His story is consistent with the evidence. 他的说法与证据一致。\n搭配: consistent with 与...一致\n同义词: constant, steady","adj. consistently (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","consolidate - 巩固，合并，统一","The company plans to consolidate its market position. 公司计划巩固其市场地位。\n搭配: consolidate power 巩固权力\n同义词: strengthen, merge","v. consolidates, consolidating, consolidated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","contemplate - 沉思，考虑，打算","She contemplated her future career path. 她思考了自己未来的职业道路。\n搭配: contemplate doing sth. 考虑做某事\n同义词: consider, ponder","v. contemplates, contemplating, contemplated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","contemporary - 当代的，同时代的","Contemporary art often challenges traditional boundaries. 当代艺术经常挑战传统边界。\n搭配: contemporary literature 当代文学\n同义词: modern, current","adj./n. contemporaries","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","contradict - 矛盾，反驳，否定","The witness's statement contradicted the evidence. 证人的陈述与证据矛盾。\n搭配: contradict each other 互相矛盾\n同义词: oppose, deny","v. contradicts, contradicting, contradicted","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","controversy - 争论，争议","The new policy caused much controversy. 新政策引起了很多争议。\n搭配: cause controversy 引起争议\n同义词: debate, dispute","n. controversies","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","convention - 大会，惯例，公约","The Geneva Convention protects prisoners of war. 《日内瓦公约》保护战俘。\n搭配: social convention 社会习俗\n同义词: tradition, custom","n. conventions","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","cooperative - 合作的，协力的","The staff was very cooperative during the audit. 员工在审计期间非常配合。\n搭配: cooperative effort 合作努力\n同义词: collaborative, helpful","adj. cooperatively (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","coordinate - 协调，配合，坐标","We need to coordinate our efforts to succeed. 我们需要协调努力才能成功。\n搭配: coordinate with 与...协调\n同义词: organize, harmonize","v./n./adj. coordinates, coordinating, coordinated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","corporate - 公司的，法人的","Corporate culture plays a vital role in employee satisfaction. 企业文化在员工满意度中起重要作用。\n搭配: corporate strategy 企业战略\n同义词: business, company","adj. corporately (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","correspond - 符合，通信，相应","The results correspond to our expectations. 结果与我们的期望相符。\n搭配: correspond with 与...通信\n同义词: match, agree","v. corresponds, corresponding, corresponded","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","corrupt - 腐败的，贪污的","The corrupt officials were arrested. 腐败官员被逮捕了。\n搭配: corrupt government 腐败政府\n同义词: dishonest, fraudulent","adj./v. corrupts, corrupting, corrupted","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","crucial - 关键的，至关重要的","Education is crucial for social development. 教育对社会发展至关重要。\n搭配: crucial factor 关键因素\n同义词: vital, essential","adj. crucially (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","cumulative - 累积的，渐增的","The cumulative effect of pollution is devastating. 污染的累积效应是毁灭性的。\n搭配: cumulative effect 累积效应\n同义词: accumulated, growing","adj. cumulatively (adv.)","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","deceive - 欺骗，蒙骗","He deceived his friends about his true intentions. 他欺骗了朋友关于他的真实意图。\n搭配: deceive sb. into doing sth. 欺骗某人做某事\n同义词: cheat, mislead","v. deceives, deceiving, deceived","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","deliberate - 故意的，深思熟虑的","It was a deliberate decision to change careers. 换职业是一个深思熟虑的决定。\n搭配: deliberate on 仔细考虑\n同义词: intentional, careful","adj./v. deliberately (adv.)","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","demonstrate - 证明，展示，示威","The experiment demonstrated the theory. 实验证明了该理论。\n搭配: demonstrate against 示威反对\n同义词: show, prove","v. demonstrates, demonstrating, demonstrated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","deny - 否认，拒绝","He denied all the charges against him. 他否认了所有对他的指控。\n搭配: deny doing sth. 否认做某事\n同义词: reject, refuse","v. denies, denying, denied","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","deprive - 剥夺，使丧失","The war deprived many children of their childhood. 战争剥夺了许多孩子的童年。\n搭配: deprive sb. of sth. 剥夺某人的某物\n同义词: strip, rob","v. deprives, depriving, deprived","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","derive - 获得，源于，衍生","Many English words derive from Latin. 许多英语单词源于拉丁语。\n搭配: derive from 源于\n同义词: obtain, originate","v. derives, deriving, derived","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","deteriorate - 恶化，变坏","His health deteriorated rapidly after the surgery. 手术后他的健康迅速恶化。\n搭配: deteriorate into 恶化为\n同义词: worsen, decline","v. deteriorates, deteriorating, deteriorated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","diminish - 减少，缩小，降低","Nothing could diminish her enthusiasm. 什么也不能减少她的热情。\n搭配: diminish over time 随时间减少\n同义词: decrease, reduce","v. diminishes, diminishing, diminished","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","discipline - 纪律，学科，训练","Mathematics is a fundamental discipline. 数学是一门基础学科。\n搭配: maintain discipline 维持纪律\n同义词: training, field","n./v. disciplines, disciplining, disciplined","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","discriminate - 歧视，区分","It's illegal to discriminate based on race or gender. 基于种族或性别歧视是违法的。\n搭配: discriminate against 歧视\n同义词: differentiate, distinguish","v. discriminates, discriminating, discriminated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","displace - 取代，转移，迫使离开","Technology has displaced many traditional jobs. 技术取代了许多传统工作。\n搭配: displaced person 流离失所者\n同义词: replace, remove","v. displaces, displacing, displaced","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","dispose - 处理，安排，倾向于","Please dispose of the waste properly. 请妥善处理废物。\n搭配: dispose of 处理\n同义词: arrange, get rid of","v. disposes, disposing, disposed","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","distinct - 明显的，独特的，不同的","There is a distinct difference between the two. 两者之间有显著差异。\n搭配: distinct from 与...不同\n同义词: clear, different","adj. distinctly (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","distort - 扭曲，歪曲，变形","The media often distorts the facts. 媒体经常歪曲事实。\n搭配: distort the truth 歪曲真相\n同义词: twist, misrepresent","v. distorts, distorting, distorted","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","distribute - 分配，分发，分布","The charity distributed food to the homeless. 慈善机构向无家可归者分发食物。\n搭配: distribute among 在...中分配\n同义词: spread, allocate","v. distributes, distributing, distributed","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","diverse - 多样的，不同的","The city has a diverse population. 这座城市有多样化的人口。\n搭配: diverse culture 多元文化\n同义词: varied, different","adj. diversely (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","dominate - 支配，统治，占优势","The team dominated the entire match. 这支球队主导了整场比赛。\n搭配: dominate the market 主导市场\n同义词: control, rule","v. dominates, dominating, dominated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","drastic - 激烈的，严厉的","The government took drastic measures to control inflation. 政府采取了严厉措施控制通货膨胀。\n搭配: drastic change 剧烈变化\n同义词: extreme, severe","adj. drastically (adv.)","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","duration - 持续，期间","The duration of the flight is about 12 hours. 飞行时间约为12小时。\n搭配: for the duration of 在...期间\n同义词: length, period","n. (uncountable)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","elaborate - 精心制作的，详尽的","She gave an elaborate explanation of the process. 她对过程做了详尽的解释。\n搭配: elaborate on 详细说明\n同义词: detailed, intricate","adj./v. elaborates, elaborating, elaborated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","eliminate - 消除，排除，淘汰","The program aims to eliminate poverty. 该计划旨在消除贫困。\n搭配: eliminate from 从...中消除\n同义词: remove, eradicate","v. eliminates, eliminating, eliminated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","emerge - 出现，浮现，暴露","New evidence emerged during the investigation. 调查期间出现了新证据。\n搭配: emerge from 从...中出现\n同义词: appear, surface","v. emerges, emerging, emerged","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","emphasize - 强调，着重","The teacher emphasized the importance of practice. 老师强调了练习的重要性。\n搭配: emphasize the need 强调需要\n同义词: stress, highlight","v. emphasizes, emphasizing, emphasized","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","empower - 授权，使能够","Education empowers people to change their lives. 教育赋予人们改变生活的能力。\n搭配: empower sb. to do sth. 授权某人做某事\n同义词: enable, authorize","v. empowers, empowering, empowered","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","encompass - 包含，包围，涵盖","The course encompasses a wide range of topics. 课程涵盖了广泛的主题。\n搭配: encompass all aspects 涵盖所有方面\n同义词: include, cover","v. encompasses, encompassing, encompassed","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","endeavor - 努力，尽力，尝试","We will endeavor to improve our service. 我们将努力改善服务。\n搭配: make every endeavor 尽一切努力\n同义词: effort, attempt","n./v. endeavors, endeavoring, endeavored","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","enforce - 执行，实施，强制","The police enforce the law. 警察执行法律。\n搭配: enforce a rule 执行规则\n同义词: implement, impose","v. enforces, enforcing, enforced","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","enhance - 提高，增强，美化","Regular exercise can enhance your immune system. 定期锻炼可以增强免疫系统。\n搭配: enhance the quality 提高质量\n同义词: improve, strengthen","v. enhances, enhancing, enhanced","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","enormous - 巨大的，庞大的","The project requires an enormous amount of funding. 该项目需要大量资金。\n搭配: enormous pressure 巨大压力\n同义词: huge, massive","adj. enormously (adv.)","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","essential - 必要的，本质的","Water is essential for life. 水对生命至关重要。\n搭配: be essential to 对...必不可少\n同义词: necessary, vital","adj. essentially (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","establish - 建立，确立，确定","The company was established in 1995. 公司成立于1995年。\n搭配: establish a reputation 建立声誉\n同义词: found, set up","v. establishes, establishing, established","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","evaluate - 评估，评价","The teacher evaluated the students' performance. 老师评估了学生的表现。\n搭配: evaluate the effectiveness 评估有效性\n同义词: assess, judge","v. evaluates, evaluating, evaluated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","evidence - 证据，迹象，明显","There is strong evidence supporting the theory. 有强有力的证据支持该理论。\n搭配: provide evidence 提供证据\n同义词: proof, indication","n. (uncountable)","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","evolve - 进化，发展，逐渐形成","Languages evolve over time over centuries. 语言在几个世纪中不断演变。\n搭配: evolve from 从...进化\n同义词: develop, progress","v. evolves, evolving, evolved","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","exaggerate - 夸大，夸张","Don't exaggerate the difficulties. 不要夸大困难。\n搭配: exaggerate the importance 夸大重要性\n同义词: overstate, overemphasize","v. exaggerates, exaggerating, exaggerated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","excellent - 优秀的，卓越的","She received excellent grades in all subjects. 她所有科目都取得了优异成绩。\n搭配: excellent performance 出色表现\n同义词: outstanding, superb","adj. excellently (adv.)","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","exception - 例外，除外","There are exceptions to every rule. 每条规则都有例外。\n搭配: with the exception of 除...之外\n同义词: exclusion, anomaly","n. exceptions","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","excessive - 过度的，过多的","Excessive drinking is harmful to health. 过度饮酒有害健康。\n搭配: excessive consumption 过度消费\n同义词: extreme, too much","adj. excessively (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","exclude - 排除，不包括，排斥","The price excludes tax. 价格不含税。\n搭配: exclude from 从...中排除\n同义词: omit, bar","v. excludes, excluding, excluded","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","exotic - 异国情调的，外来的","The market sells exotic fruits from Southeast Asia. 市场出售来自东南亚的异国水果。\n搭配: exotic destination 异国目的地\n同义词: foreign, unusual","adj. exotically (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","expand - 扩大，扩展，膨胀","The company plans to expand into Asian markets. 公司计划扩展到亚洲市场。\n搭配: expand business 扩大业务\n同义词: enlarge, grow","v. expands, expanding, expanded","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","expert - 专家，熟练的","She is an expert in computer science. 她是计算机科学专家。\n搭配: expert advice 专家建议\n同义词: specialist, professional","n./adj. (no comparative)","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","explicit - 明确的，清楚的，直言的","The instructions were explicit and easy to follow. 说明明确且易于遵循。\n搭配: explicit instruction 明确指示\n同义词: clear, direct","adj. explicitly (adv.)","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","exploit - 开发，利用，剥削","Companies should not exploit their workers. 公司不应该剥削工人。\n搭配: exploit resources 开发资源\n同义词: utilize, take advantage of","v./n. exploits, exploiting, exploited","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","extract - 提取，摘录，拔出","The dentist extracted his bad tooth. 牙医拔掉了他的坏牙。\n搭配: extract from 从...中提取\n同义词: remove, obtain","v./n. extracts, extracting, extracted","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","facilitate - 促进，使容易，帮助","Technology facilitates communication. 技术促进了交流。\n搭配: facilitate learning 促进学习\n同义词: assist, enable","v. facilitates, facilitating, facilitated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","factor - 因素，要素，因子","Many factors contribute to climate change. 许多因素导致气候变化。\n搭配: key factor 关键因素\n同义词: element, component","n. factors","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","fascinate - 迷住，强烈吸引","The audience was fascinated by the performance. 观众被表演迷住了。\n搭配: be fascinated by 被...迷住\n同义词: captivate, charm","v. fascinates, fascinating, fascinated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","feasible - 可行的，行得通的","The plan is feasible within our budget. 该计划在我们的预算内是可行的。\n搭配: feasible solution 可行方案\n同义词: possible, practical","adj. feasibly (adv.)","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","feature - 特征，特色，特写","The phone's best feature is its camera. 这款手机最好的特点是它的摄像头。\n搭配: feature film 故事片\n同义词: characteristic, attribute","n./v. features, featuring, featured","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","fertile - 肥沃的，能繁殖的","The fertile soil produces abundant crops. 肥沃的土壤产出丰富的作物。\n搭配: fertile imagination 丰富的想象力\n同义词: productive, rich","adj. fertility (n.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","flexible - 灵活的，柔韧的","We need a more flexible approach to the problem. 我们需要更灵活的方法来解决这个问题。\n搭配: flexible schedule 灵活的时间表\n同义词: adaptable, adjustable","adj. flexibly (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","fluctuate - 波动，涨落，起伏","Oil prices fluctuate daily. 石油价格每天都在波动。\n搭配: fluctuate between 在...之间波动\n同义词: vary, change","v. fluctuates, fluctuating, fluctuated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","focus - 焦点，集中，关注","The focus of the discussion was on education. 讨论的重点是教育。\n搭配: focus on 集中\n同义词: center, concentrate","n./v. focuses, focusing, focused","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","forbid - 禁止，不许","Smoking is forbidden in the building. 大楼内禁止吸烟。\n搭配: forbid sb. to do sth. 禁止某人做某事\n同义词: prohibit, ban","v. forbids, forbidding, forbade/forbidden","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","format - 格式，版式，格式化","Please submit your essay in PDF format. 请以PDF格式提交论文。\n搭配: file format 文件格式\n同义词: layout, structure","n./v. formats, formatting, formatted","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","formulate - 制定，规划，确切表达","The committee formulated a new policy. 委员会制定了新政策。\n搭配: formulate a plan 制定计划\n同义词: develop, create","v. formulates, formulating, formulated","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","foster - 培养，促进，收养","The program aims to foster creativity in children. 该计划旨在培养儿童的创造力。\n搭配: foster cooperation 促进合作\n同义词: promote, encourage","v. fosters, fostering, fostered","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","foundation - 基础，基金会，建立","A good education provides a solid foundation for the future. 良好的教育为未来提供了坚实的基础。\n搭配: lay the foundation 奠定基础\n同义词: basis, groundwork","n. foundations","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","framework - 框架，体系，结构","The report provides a framework for future research. 报告为未来研究提供了框架。\n搭配: legal framework 法律框架\n同义词: structure, system","n. frameworks","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","fundamental - 基本的，根本的","There is a fundamental difference between the two approaches. 两种方法之间有根本区别。\n搭配: fundamental right 基本权利\n同义词: basic, essential","adj. fundamentally (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","generate - 产生，生成，引起","The project will generate many new jobs. 该项目将创造许多新工作岗位。\n搭配: generate electricity 发电\n同义词: produce, create","v. generates, generating, generated","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","genuine - 真正的，真诚的","She showed genuine concern for the victims. 她对受害者表现出真诚的关心。\n搭配: genuine leather 真皮\n同义词: real, authentic","adj. genuinely (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","global - 全球的，全面的","Climate change is a global issue. 气候变化是一个全球性问题。\n搭配: global economy 全球经济\n同义词: worldwide, international","adj. globally (adv.)","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","grant - 授予，同意，拨款","The university granted her a scholarship. 大学授予她奖学金。\n搭配: take for granted 认为理所当然\n同义词: give, award","v./n. grants, granting, granted","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","guarantee - 保证，担保，保修","The product comes with a two-year guarantee. 该产品有两年的保修期。\n搭配: guarantee quality 保证质量\n同义词: promise, warrant","v./n. guarantees, guaranteeing, guaranteed","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","habitat - 栖息地，自然环境","Deforestation destroys the natural habitat of many species. 森林砍伐破坏了许多物种的自然栖息地。\n搭配: natural habitat 自然栖息地\n同义词: environment, home","n. habitats","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","harness - 利用，治理，驾驭","We need to harness renewable energy sources. 我们需要利用可再生能源。\n搭配: harness the power 利用力量\n同义词: utilize, exploit","v. harnesses, harnessing, harnessed","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","hazard - 危险，危害，冒险","Smoking is a health hazard. 吸烟是一种健康危害。\n搭配: health hazard 健康危害\n同义词: danger, risk","n./v. hazards, hazarding, hazarded","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","hierarchy - 等级制度，层级","The company has a strict hierarchy. 公司有严格的等级制度。\n搭配: social hierarchy 社会等级\n同义词: ranking, pecking order","n. hierarchies","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","highlight - 突出，强调，亮点","The report highlighted the main findings. 报告突出了主要发现。\n搭配: highlight the importance 强调重要性\n同义词: emphasize, stress","v./n. highlights, highlighting, highlighted","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","hinder - 阻碍，妨碍","Bad weather hindered the rescue efforts. 恶劣天气阻碍了救援工作。\n搭配: hinder progress 阻碍进步\n同义词: obstruct, impede","v. hinders, hindering, hindered","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","hypothesis - 假设，假说","The scientist tested her hypothesis through experiments. 科学家通过实验检验了她的假设。\n搭配: test a hypothesis 检验假设\n同义词: theory, assumption","n. hypotheses","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","identical - 相同的，完全一样的","The twins look identical. 这对双胞胎看起来一模一样。\n搭配: identical to 与...相同\n同义词: same, matching","adj. identically (adv.)","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","identify - 识别，确定，认同","The police identified the suspect. 警方确认了嫌疑人。\n搭配: identify with 认同\n同义词: recognize, determine","v. identifies, identifying, identified","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","ignite - 点燃，引发，激起","The speech ignited a wave of protests. 演讲引发了一波抗议。\n搭配: ignite passion 点燃激情\n同义词: spark, trigger","v. ignites, igniting, ignited","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","illusion - 幻觉，错觉","The mirage created an illusion of water. 海市蜃楼造成了水的错觉。\n搭配: optical illusion 视觉错觉\n同义词: delusion, fantasy","n. illusions","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Vocabulary","illustrate - 说明，阐明，加插图","The example illustrates the point well. 这个例子很好地说明了这一点。\n搭配: illustrate with 用...说明\n同义词: demonstrate, explain","v. illustrates, illustrating, illustrated","Medium"),
