    reading = [
        ("CET-4","Reading","Passage 1: The Benefits of Reading","Reading is one of the most beneficial habits a person can develop. Studies have shown that regular reading improves vocabulary, enhances concentration, and reduces stress. According to a study conducted by the University of Sussex, reading for just six minutes can reduce stress levels by up to 68%. Furthermore, reading fiction has been shown to increase empathy and emotional intelligence.\n\nQuestions:\n1. According to the passage, how much can reading reduce stress levels?\n   A. Up to 50%  B. Up to 68%  C. Up to 75%  D. Up to 80%\n2. What type of reading increases empathy?\n   A. Non-fiction  B. Newspapers  C. Fiction  D. Textbooks","1. B  2. C","Medium"),
        ("CET-4","Reading","Passage 2: Climate Change and Its Effects","Climate change is one of the most pressing issues facing our planet today. Global temperatures have risen by approximately 1.1 degrees Celsius since pre-industrial times. This warming has led to more frequent extreme weather events, rising sea levels, and disruptions to ecosystems worldwide. Scientists warn that without significant reductions in greenhouse gas emissions, the effects of climate change will become increasingly severe.\n\nQuestions:\n1. How much have global temperatures risen since pre-industrial times?\n   A. 0.5°C  B. 0.8°C  C. 1.1°C  D. 1.5°C\n2. What do scientists warn about?\n   A. More rainfall  B. Increasing severity of effects  C. Cooling trends  D. Stable weather","1. C  2. B","Medium"),
        ("CET-4","Reading","Passage 3: The History of the Internet","The Internet has revolutionized the way we communicate, work, and live. It began as a military project in the 1960s called ARPANET. By the 1990s, the World Wide Web had been invented by Tim Berners-Lee, making the Internet accessible to the general public. Today, over 5 billion people worldwide use the Internet, and it has become an essential part of daily life.\n\nQuestions:\n1. When did the Internet begin as a military project?\n   A. 1950s  B. 1960s  C. 1970s  D. 1980s\n2. Who invented the World Wide Web?\n   A. Bill Gates  B. Steve Jobs  C. Tim Berners-Lee  D. Mark Zuckerberg","1. B  2. C","Easy"),
        ("CET-4","Reading","Passage 4: Healthy Eating Habits","Maintaining a balanced diet is essential for good health. Nutritionists recommend eating at least five portions of fruits and vegetables daily. Whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats should also be included in one's diet. Avoiding processed foods and excessive sugar can significantly reduce the risk of chronic diseases such as diabetes and heart disease.\n\nQuestions:\n1. How many portions of fruits and vegetables are recommended daily?\n   A. Three  B. Four  C. Five  D. Six\n2. What can excessive sugar increase the risk of?\n   A. Broken bones  B. Chronic diseases  C. Allergies  D. Insomnia","1. C  2. B","Easy"),
        ("CET-4","Reading","Passage 5: Artificial Intelligence","Artificial Intelligence (AI) is transforming industries across the globe. From healthcare to finance, AI is being used to automate tasks, analyze data, and make predictions. While AI offers many benefits, there are also concerns about job displacement and ethical implications. Experts believe that AI will create new jobs even as it eliminates others.\n\nQuestions:\n1. What is one concern about AI?\n   A. Too expensive  B. Job displacement  C. Too slow  D. Limited use\n2. What do experts believe about AI and jobs?\n   A. AI will eliminate all jobs  B. AI will create new jobs  C. AI has no impact on jobs  D. AI only affects manual labor","1. B  2. B","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Reading","Passage 1: The Psychology of Decision Making","Human decision-making is a complex process influenced by cognitive biases, emotions, and social factors. Research in behavioral economics has shown that people often make irrational decisions due to biases such as confirmation bias, anchoring effect, and loss aversion. Understanding these biases can help individuals make better decisions in their personal and professional lives.\n\nQuestions:\n1. What field studies irrational decision-making?\n   A. Neuroscience  B. Behavioral economics  C. Social psychology  D. Cognitive science\n2. Which bias involves relying too heavily on the first piece of information?\n   A. Confirmation bias  B. Loss aversion  C. Anchoring effect  D. Hindsight bias","1. B  2. C","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Reading","Passage 2: Sustainable Development","Sustainable development seeks to meet the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs. This concept encompasses three pillars: economic growth, social inclusion, and environmental protection. The United Nations has established 17 Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) to be achieved by 2030.\n\nQuestions:\n1. How many Sustainable Development Goals has the UN established?\n   A. 10  B. 15  C. 17  D. 20\n2. Which of the following is NOT a pillar of sustainable development?\n   A. Economic growth  B. Social inclusion  C. Military expansion  D. Environmental protection","1. C  2. C","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Reading","Passage 3: The Future of Work","The nature of work is changing rapidly due to technological advancement and globalization. Remote work has become increasingly common, accelerated by the COVID-19 pandemic. Many companies are adopting hybrid work models that combine in-office and remote work. This shift has implications for work-life balance, productivity, and employee well-being.\n\nQuestions:\n1. What accelerated the adoption of remote work?\n   A. Economic recession  B. COVID-19 pandemic  C. New labor laws  D. Climate change\n2. What is a hybrid work model?\n   A. Working only from home  B. Combining in-office and remote work  C. Working multiple jobs  D. Flexible hours only","1. B  2. B","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Reading","Passage 4: Biodiversity Loss","Biodiversity loss is one of the most critical environmental challenges of our time. Scientists estimate that species are going extinct at 1,000 times the natural rate. Habitat destruction, climate change, pollution, and overexploitation are the main drivers of this loss. Protecting biodiversity is essential for ecosystem stability and human survival.\n\nQuestions:\n1. How much faster are species going extinct compared to the natural rate?\n   A. 100 times  B. 500 times  C. 1,000 times  D. 10,000 times\n2. Which is NOT mentioned as a driver of biodiversity loss?\n   A. Habitat destruction  B. Climate change  C. Space exploration  D. Pollution","1. C  2. C","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Reading","Passage 5: The Gig Economy","The gig economy refers to a labor market characterized by short-term contracts and freelance work rather than permanent jobs. Platforms like Uber, Fiverr, and Upwork have facilitated this shift. While the gig economy offers flexibility, it also raises concerns about job security, benefits, and worker rights. Governments worldwide are grappling with how to regulate this new form of employment.\n\nQuestions:\n1. What characterizes the gig economy?\n   A. Permanent jobs  B. Short-term contracts  C. Government employment  D. Unionized labor\n2. What is a concern about the gig economy?\n   A. Too much flexibility  B. Job security  C. Too many benefits  D. Over-regulation","1. B  2. B","Hard"),
    ]
    
    listening = [
        ("CET-4","Listening","Conversation 1: At the Airport","W: Excuse me, could you tell me where Gate 15 is?\nM: Sure, go straight down this corridor and turn left at the bookstore. Gate 15 will be on your right.\nW: Thank you. Is there a coffee shop nearby?\nM: Yes, there's one just past the bookstore on the left.\n\nQuestions:\n1. Where does the woman want to go?\n   A. Gate 10  B. Gate 15  C. Gate 20  D. The bookstore\n2. Where is the coffee shop?\n   A. On the right  B. At Gate 15  C. Past the bookstore on the left  D. Near the entrance","1. B  2. C","Easy"),
        ("CET-4","Listening","Conversation 2: Job Interview","M: Thank you for coming in today. Can you tell me about your previous work experience?\nW: I worked as a marketing assistant at ABC Company for two years. I was responsible for social media campaigns and content creation.\nM: That sounds relevant. What software are you proficient in?\nW: I'm skilled in Photoshop, Excel, and various social media management tools.\n\nQuestions:\n1. What was the woman's previous job?\n   A. Sales manager  B. Marketing assistant  C. Content writer  D. Social media manager\n2. What software does she mention?\n   A. Word  B. PowerPoint  C. Photoshop  D. Illustrator","1. B  2. C","Medium"),
        ("CET-4","Listening","Passage 3: News Report","Good evening. In today's news, the city council has approved a new public transportation plan. The plan includes the construction of two new subway lines and the expansion of the bus network. The project is expected to cost $2.5 billion and will be completed over the next five years. Officials say the new system will reduce traffic congestion by 30%.\n\nQuestions:\n1. What has the city council approved?\n   A. A new highway  B. A new public transportation plan  C. A new airport  D. A new park\n2. How much will the project cost?\n   A. $1.5 billion  B. $2 billion  C. $2.5 billion  D. $3 billion","1. B  2. C","Medium"),
        ("CET-6","Listening","Lecture 1: The Science of Sleep","Sleep is essential for physical and mental health. During sleep, the body repairs tissues, consolidates memories, and regulates hormones. Adults need 7-9 hours of sleep per night. Chronic sleep deprivation has been linked to obesity, heart disease, and depression. Recent research suggests that the brain's glymphatic system, which clears waste products, is most active during sleep.\n\nQuestions:\n1. How much sleep do adults need per night?\n   A. 5-7 hours  B. 6-8 hours  C. 7-9 hours  D. 8-10 hours\n2. What system is most active during sleep?\n   A. Immune system  B. Glymphatic system  C. Digestive system  D. Respiratory system","1. C  2. B","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Listening","Lecture 2: Urbanization Trends","By 2050, it is estimated that 68% of the world's population will live in urban areas. This rapid urbanization presents both opportunities and challenges. Cities are centers of innovation and economic growth, but they also face issues such as housing shortages, traffic congestion, and pollution. Urban planners are working to create more sustainable and livable cities through smart city technologies.\n\nQuestions:\n1. What percentage of the world's population will live in urban areas by 2050?\n   A. 55%  B. 60%  C. 68%  D. 75%\n2. What are urban planners using to create better cities?\n   A. Traditional methods  B. Smart city technologies  C. Rural development  D. Industrial expansion","1. C  2. B","Medium"),
    ]
    
    writing = [
        ("CET-4","Writing","How to Keep Healthy","Write an essay of at least 120 words on the topic 'How to Keep Healthy'.\n\nOutline:\n1. Importance of health\n2. Ways to keep healthy\n3. Your personal habits","Sample Answer:\n\nHow to Keep Healthy\n\nHealth is the most important treasure in our life. Without good health, we cannot study, work, or enjoy life effectively.\n\nThere are many ways to keep healthy. First, we should maintain a balanced diet with plenty of fruits and vegetables. Second, regular exercise is essential. We should exercise at least three times a week. Third, getting enough sleep is crucial—at least eight hours a night. Finally, we should avoid bad habits like smoking and excessive drinking.\n\nAs for me, I jog every morning and try to eat more vegetables. I also make sure to go to bed before 11 p.m. These habits have kept me energetic and healthy.\n\nIn conclusion, health is wealth. Let's develop good habits and live a healthy life.","Medium"),
        ("CET-4","Writing","The Importance of Reading","Write an essay of at least 120 words on 'The Importance of Reading'.\n\nOutline:\n1. Why reading is important\n2. Benefits of reading\n3. How to develop reading habits","Sample Answer:\n\nThe Importance of Reading\n\nReading plays a vital role in our personal growth and development. It is one of the most effective ways to acquire knowledge and broaden our horizons.\n\nReading offers numerous benefits. First, it improves our language skills, including vocabulary and grammar. Second, reading enhances our critical thinking ability. Third, it reduces stress and helps us relax. Research shows that reading for just six minutes can reduce stress by up to 68%.\n\nTo develop reading habits, we should start with books that interest us. Setting aside 30 minutes daily for reading is a good start. We can also join a book club to share ideas with others.\n\nIn conclusion, reading is a lifelong habit that benefits us in countless ways.","Medium"),
        ("CET-4","Writing","My Favorite Season","Write an essay of at least 120 words on 'My Favorite Season'.\n\nOutline:\n1. Which season you like best\n2. Why you like it\n3. What activities you do in this season","Sample Answer:\n\nMy Favorite Season\n\nAmong the four seasons, I like autumn best. It is a season of harvest and beauty.\n\nThere are several reasons why I love autumn. First, the weather is perfect—not too hot and not too cold. Second, the scenery is breathtaking. The leaves turn golden and red, creating a beautiful landscape. Third, autumn is the season of harvest, bringing abundant fruits and vegetables.\n\nIn autumn, I enjoy many outdoor activities. I often go hiking with my friends to enjoy the colorful leaves. I also like flying kites in the park. Sometimes, I help my grandparents pick apples in their orchard.\n\nIn short, autumn is my favorite season because of its pleasant weather, beautiful scenery, and fun activities.","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Writing","The Impact of Social Media","Write an essay of at least 150 words on 'The Impact of Social Media'.\n\nOutline:\n1. The prevalence of social media\n2. Positive and negative impacts\n3. Your opinion","Sample Answer:\n\nThe Impact of Social Media\n\nSocial media has become an integral part of modern life. Platforms like WeChat, Weibo, and TikTok have billions of users worldwide, fundamentally changing how we communicate and consume information.\n\nSocial media has both positive and negative impacts. On the positive side, it connects people across distances, facilitates information sharing, and provides platforms for self-expression. It has also become a powerful tool for business marketing and social movements. On the negative side, excessive use of social media can lead to addiction, anxiety, and depression. The spread of misinformation is another serious concern.\n\nIn my opinion, social media is a double-edged sword. We should use it wisely and moderately. It is important to verify information before sharing and to maintain a healthy balance between online and offline life.\n\nIn conclusion, while social media offers many benefits, we must be aware of its potential harms and use it responsibly.","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Writing","Artificial Intelligence and the Future","Write an essay of at least 150 words on 'Artificial Intelligence and the Future'.\n\nOutline:\n1. Current applications of AI\n2. Potential impacts on society\n3. How we should prepare","Sample Answer:\n\nArtificial Intelligence and the Future\n\nArtificial Intelligence (AI) is rapidly transforming our world. From voice assistants like Siri to self-driving cars, AI applications are becoming increasingly prevalent in our daily lives.\n\nAI has the potential to bring about significant changes to society. In healthcare, AI can help diagnose diseases more accurately and develop personalized treatment plans. In education, AI-powered tools can provide personalized learning experiences. However, AI also raises concerns about job displacement and ethical issues such as privacy and bias.\n\nTo prepare for an AI-driven future, we should focus on developing skills that complement AI rather than compete with it. Creativity, critical thinking, and emotional intelligence are areas where humans excel over machines. Additionally, governments should establish regulations to ensure AI is developed and used ethically.\n\nIn conclusion, AI will play an increasingly important role in our future. By embracing its benefits while addressing its challenges, we can create a better future for all.","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Writing","Environmental Protection","Write an essay of at least 150 words on 'Environmental Protection'.\n\nOutline:\n1. Current environmental problems\n2. Causes of environmental degradation\n3. Measures to protect the environment","Sample Answer:\n\nEnvironmental Protection\n\nEnvironmental protection has become one of the most urgent issues of our time. Air pollution, water contamination, deforestation, and climate change are threatening the health of our planet.\n\nThe causes of environmental degradation are manifold. Industrialization and urbanization have led to increased emissions and waste. Overconsumption of natural resources and excessive use of plastic have further exacerbated the problem. Additionally, a lack of environmental awareness among the public has contributed to the crisis.\n\nTo protect the environment, we need to take action at multiple levels. Governments should implement stricter environmental regulations and invest in renewable energy. Companies should adopt sustainable practices and reduce their carbon footprint. Individuals can contribute by reducing waste, using public transportation, and choosing eco-friendly products.\n\nIn conclusion, environmental protection requires the collective effort of governments, businesses, and individuals. Only by working together can we preserve our planet for future generations.","Medium"),
    ]
    
    translation = [
        ("CET-4","Translation","Chinese to English: 传统文化","中国有着悠久的历史和丰富的传统文化。春节是中国最重要的传统节日，人们会贴春联、放鞭炮、吃年夜饭。中秋节是另一个重要节日，人们会赏月、吃月饼。这些传统节日不仅承载着文化内涵，也加强了家庭和社会的联系。","China has a long history and rich traditional culture. The Spring Festival is the most important traditional holiday in China, during which people put up Spring Festival couplets, set off firecrackers, and have reunion dinners. The Mid-Autumn Festival is another important holiday when people admire the moon and eat mooncakes. These traditional festivals not only carry cultural significance but also strengthen family and social bonds.","Medium"),
        ("CET-4","Translation","Chinese to English: 科技发展","随着科技的快速发展，人们的生活方式发生了巨大变化。智能手机和互联网的普及使得信息获取更加便捷。在线教育平台让学生可以随时随地学习。电子商务的兴起改变了人们的购物方式。然而，科技发展也带来了一些挑战，如网络安全问题和隐私保护。","With the rapid development of technology, people's lifestyles have undergone tremendous changes. The popularity of smartphones and the Internet has made information access more convenient. Online education platforms allow students to learn anytime and anywhere. The rise of e-commerce has changed the way people shop. However, technological development has also brought some challenges, such as cybersecurity issues and privacy protection.","Medium"),
        ("CET-4","Translation","Chinese to English: 环境保护","环境保护是当今世界面临的重要挑战之一。空气污染、水污染和土壤污染对人类健康构成了严重威胁。为了应对这些挑战，各国政府正在采取措施减少污染物排放，推广可再生能源。每个人也应该从自身做起，节约能源，减少浪费。","Environmental protection is one of the important challenges facing the world today. Air pollution, water pollution, and soil pollution pose serious threats to human health. To address these challenges, governments around the world are taking measures to reduce pollutant emissions and promote renewable energy. Everyone should also start from themselves, saving energy and reducing waste.","Easy"),
        ("CET-6","Translation","Chinese to English: 人工智能","人工智能正在深刻改变着各行各业。在医疗领域，AI可以帮助医生更准确地诊断疾病。在金融领域，AI被用于风险评估和欺诈检测。在教育领域，AI可以为学生提供个性化的学习体验。然而，AI的发展也引发了关于就业替代和伦理问题的讨论。","Artificial intelligence is profoundly transforming various industries. In healthcare, AI can help doctors diagnose diseases more accurately. In finance, AI is used for risk assessment and fraud detection. In education, AI can provide personalized learning experiences for students. However, the development of AI has also sparked discussions about job displacement and ethical issues.","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Translation","Chinese to English: 全球化","全球化使世界各国之间的联系更加紧密。国际贸易的增长促进了经济发展，文化交流增进了各国人民之间的理解。然而，全球化也带来了一些问题，如贫富差距扩大和文化同质化。因此，我们需要在全球化进程中寻求平衡，确保其惠及所有人。","Globalization has made connections between countries around the world closer. The growth of international trade has promoted economic development, and cultural exchange has enhanced understanding among people of different countries. However, globalization has also brought some problems, such as widening wealth gaps and cultural homogenization. Therefore, we need to seek a balance in the process of globalization to ensure that it benefits everyone.","Hard"),
        ("CET-6","Translation","Chinese to English: 城市化","中国的城市化进程在过去几十年中迅速推进。大量农村人口涌入城市，寻求更好的就业和生活条件。城市化带来了经济增长和基础设施改善，但也带来了交通拥堵、住房短缺和环境污染等问题。政府正在努力通过城市规划来解决这些问题。","China's urbanization process has advanced rapidly in the past few decades. A large number of rural people have flooded into cities, seeking better employment and living conditions. Urbanization has brought economic growth and infrastructure improvement, but it has also brought problems such as traffic congestion, housing shortages, and environmental pollution. The government is working to address these issues through urban planning.","Medium"),
    ]
    
    all_data = vocab + reading + listening + writing + translation
